# Memory usage percentage for pods
kubectl top pod --no-headers | awk '{print $1, $2, $3, $4, $5, ($6/$3*100)}'

# CPU usage percentage for pods
kubectl top pod --no-headers | awk '{print $1, $2, $3, $4, $5, ($7/$4*100)}'

This has now been added to the daily checklist: kubectl top nodes and kubectl top pods will give us a list of all the pods and their resource usage.
